1
00:00:08,173 --> 00:00:10,243
This district is concentrated with publishing houses, right?

2
00:00:10,243 --> 00:00:11,573
- Right. - Yes.

3
00:00:11,573 --> 00:00:13,073
It's been a while since I came here.

4
00:00:13,073 --> 00:00:14,073
- Yes. - Yes.

5
00:00:14,073 --> 00:00:15,913
(Today's spare time, Paju)

6
00:00:15,913 --> 00:00:20,053
I filmed dramas and movies in this neighborhood a few times.

7
00:00:20,053 --> 00:00:21,683
A lot of dramas and movies...

8
00:00:21,683 --> 00:00:23,023
- are shot here. Right. - Yes.

9
00:00:23,053 --> 00:00:24,553
Didn't you film a lot of your shows here too?

10
00:00:24,553 --> 00:00:27,423
I filmed a lot of shows here like "Let's Read Books."

11
00:00:27,423 --> 00:00:28,863
(That was 25 years ago.)

12
00:00:28,863 --> 00:00:30,493
- Here... - "Let's Read Books."

13
00:00:30,523 --> 00:00:32,263
I came here a lot when I was filming that show.

14
00:00:32,693 --> 00:00:33,863
We shot the show here in Paju Book City.

15
00:00:33,863 --> 00:00:36,203
- Right. - Yes. I used to come here often.

16
00:00:36,203 --> 00:00:37,433
(The two MCs are familiar with today's spot, Paju.)

17
00:00:37,433 --> 00:00:39,703
I wonder if today's guests have ties to this area too.

18
00:00:39,703 --> 00:00:41,033
Do you know who's joining us today?

19
00:00:41,073 --> 00:00:43,443
Yes. I heard about today's guests.

20
00:00:43,443 --> 00:00:45,243
- Wait, you don't know who they are? - I don't.

21
00:00:45,243 --> 00:00:46,843
(Jae Suk doesn't know about today's guests.)

22
00:00:46,843 --> 00:00:48,443
- They're from my industry. - Right?

23
00:00:48,443 --> 00:00:50,043
- Yes. - Right.

24
00:00:50,043 --> 00:00:53,083
And the two of them recently filmed a variety show.

25
00:00:53,083 --> 00:00:55,023
- Wait. Really? - Yes.

26
00:00:55,783 --> 00:00:57,353
Are they here to promote a drama?

27
00:00:57,353 --> 00:00:59,323
No. I don't think they're here to promote a drama.

28
00:00:59,323 --> 00:01:00,623
- Really? - Yes.

29
00:01:00,893 --> 00:01:02,723
I think the two of them got close...

30
00:01:02,723 --> 00:01:04,063
while filming the variety show.

31
00:01:04,063 --> 00:01:05,063
They bonded...

32
00:01:05,063 --> 00:01:06,333
- on the variety show? - Yes.

33
00:01:06,333 --> 00:01:07,963
Really? Not in a drama or a movie?

34
00:01:08,133 --> 00:01:10,963
I'm sure you'll be happy to see them.

35
00:01:10,963 --> 00:01:11,973
- Really? - Yes.

36
00:01:11,973 --> 00:01:13,703
At this point, why don't you just tell me?

37
00:01:14,433 --> 00:01:16,373
Why is Yeon Shik giving me a riddle?

38
00:01:16,373 --> 00:01:17,773
You don't share information with me either.

39
00:01:17,773 --> 00:01:19,143
What are you talking about?

40
00:01:19,143 --> 00:01:20,373
Did you always tell me about the guests?

41
00:01:20,373 --> 00:01:23,513
You know what? There's a reason the staff keeps this a secret.

42
00:01:23,513 --> 00:01:25,183
- Why? - I just don't want to share it.

43
00:01:25,183 --> 00:01:26,253
You don't?

44
00:01:26,883 --> 00:01:29,023
For some reason, I want to be the only one who knows.

45
00:01:29,023 --> 00:01:31,223
You know what? Curiosity doesn't get the better of me.

46
00:01:31,483 --> 00:01:33,223
I'll meet them soon enough.

47
00:01:34,293 --> 00:01:36,793
We have to wait for a long time to catch the bus here.

48
00:01:36,963 --> 00:01:38,833
- A lot of people live in Paju. - Yes.

49
00:01:38,893 --> 00:01:40,393
Paju is a great place to live.

50
00:01:40,493 --> 00:01:41,563
- Right? - Yes.

51
00:01:41,663 --> 00:01:42,863
You somehow made it possible to come today.

52
00:01:42,963 --> 00:01:45,333
Pardon? Oh, it's a wordplay for "Whenever Possible."

53
00:01:45,333 --> 00:01:46,333
(Chuckling)

54
00:01:46,333 --> 00:01:47,873
It's about time you got used to this.

55
00:01:47,873 --> 00:01:50,303
(They approach while chatting friendly.)

56
00:01:50,543 --> 00:01:53,443
They bonded on a variety show, not in a drama or a movie.

57
00:01:53,443 --> 00:01:54,473
- So they're joining us together. - Okay.

58
00:01:54,473 --> 00:01:55,883
- They're here. - Oh, there they are.

59
00:01:55,883 --> 00:01:56,913
There are so many cameras.

60
00:01:57,583 --> 00:01:59,413
- Hello. - My gosh, Mi Ran.

61
00:01:59,413 --> 00:02:00,453
Hey, Yang Se Chan.

62
00:02:00,453 --> 00:02:02,183
(Today's Whenever Friends: Ra Mi Ran and Joo Jong Hyuk)

63
00:02:03,183 --> 00:02:05,093
(I'm Ra Mi Ran, the singing cheetah.)

64
00:02:05,553 --> 00:02:08,293
(She can dominate the scenes even without any music.)

65
00:02:09,363 --> 00:02:14,793
(The queen of comedy knows how to kill it on screen.)

66
00:02:15,733 --> 00:02:18,473
(The talented actress can pull off any genre.)

67
00:02:18,473 --> 00:02:21,803
(Actress Ra Mi Ran)

68
00:02:22,873 --> 00:02:26,013
(He played Kwon Min Woo, the trickster.)

69
00:02:26,813 --> 00:02:30,183
(He made his unlikable character unforgettable.)

70
00:02:31,983 --> 00:02:34,553
(His acting was superb in all of his projects.)

71
00:02:34,583 --> 00:02:37,853
(Actor Joo Jong Hyuk)

72
00:02:38,693 --> 00:02:41,723
(They met as the CEO and manager of a beauty salon on a show.)

73
00:02:43,493 --> 00:02:46,063
(Their perfect chemistry was forged.)

74
00:02:46,533 --> 00:02:49,963
(That's how they became close friends.)

75
00:02:51,633 --> 00:02:52,633
This is Sook's good friend.

76
00:02:52,773 --> 00:02:54,373
- Hello. - My gosh.

77
00:02:54,373 --> 00:02:56,403
- It's been a while. - She's Sook's close friend.

78
00:02:56,543 --> 00:02:58,443
- Hey, Se Chan. Jong Hyuk. - Have you been well?

79
00:02:59,373 --> 00:03:01,173
- Hello. - Nice to meet you. I'm Jong Hyuk.

80
00:03:01,173 --> 00:03:02,313
- Why do you call him Se Chan? - Right.

81
00:03:02,443 --> 00:03:03,883
- He resembles Se Chan. - But...

82
00:03:03,983 --> 00:03:05,653
- There's a resemblance. - Yes, there is.

83
00:03:05,653 --> 00:03:06,753
- There is. - Right.

84
00:03:06,753 --> 00:03:08,183
He looks nothing like Se Chan.

85
00:03:08,183 --> 00:03:10,483
- He's much more handsome. - He is.

86
00:03:10,623 --> 00:03:11,923
You should see them together.

87
00:03:12,353 --> 00:03:13,593
- He and Se Chan look alike. - Gosh.

88
00:03:13,593 --> 00:03:14,653
- Really? - Yes.

89
00:03:14,923 --> 00:03:16,863
- When you guys are together? - Yes.

90
00:03:17,523 --> 00:03:20,333
- You guys look alike. Right? - Right. Actually,

91
00:03:20,533 --> 00:03:22,603
I starred on "Running Man" to prove people wrong.

92
00:03:23,003 --> 00:03:24,263
- But I couldn't prove them wrong. - Rather, he confirmed it.

93
00:03:24,263 --> 00:03:25,303
- I did? - Yes.

94
00:03:25,303 --> 00:03:26,373
He came to prove us wrong,

95
00:03:26,373 --> 00:03:27,433
- but he confirmed it. - Right, I did.

96
00:03:27,733 --> 00:03:29,003
There's a slight resemblance.

97
00:03:29,003 --> 00:03:31,003
- I just saw a glimpse of Se Chan. - Yes.

98
00:03:31,003 --> 00:03:32,613
My gosh, Jong Hyuk does resemble him.

99
00:03:33,373 --> 00:03:35,743
Why don't you draw his signature beard?

100
00:03:35,743 --> 00:03:38,853
- He's famous for that beard. - That's already been done with CGI.

101
00:03:38,853 --> 00:03:39,883
- Oh, really? - Yes.

102
00:03:39,883 --> 00:03:41,583
(The beard CGI was already done.)

103
00:03:41,583 --> 00:03:44,653
- It's been done. - And they kept using the CGI.

104
00:03:44,853 --> 00:03:46,923
- On "Running Man?" - Yes. They kept using it.

105
00:03:48,993 --> 00:03:51,763
By the way, I thought you guys shot...

106
00:03:51,763 --> 00:03:53,693
a drama or movie together...

107
00:03:53,693 --> 00:03:55,203
- when I heard you were joining us. - Right.

108
00:03:55,303 --> 00:03:57,063
Come to think of it, we've never acted together...

109
00:03:57,063 --> 00:03:58,203
- Not even once? - No.

110
00:03:58,203 --> 00:04:00,073
- We met on a variety show. - What about with Yeon Seok?

111
00:04:00,073 --> 00:04:03,773
When she was filming "Reply" series, I visited the shoot.

112
00:04:03,773 --> 00:04:07,273
- We said hello to each other. - He sent us a coffee truck.

113
00:04:07,443 --> 00:04:08,473
What about you, Jong Hyuk?

114
00:04:08,473 --> 00:04:11,083
- It's our 1st time meeting today. - It's our 1st time.

115
00:04:11,213 --> 00:04:12,653
I guess I'm closer to Jong Hyuk...

116
00:04:12,653 --> 00:04:14,053
- than you are. - Right.

117
00:04:14,053 --> 00:04:15,183
But I feel like...

118
00:04:15,183 --> 00:04:16,653
- we're already friends... - Right.

119
00:04:16,653 --> 00:04:18,753
- thanks to Se Chan. - Right.

120
00:04:18,953 --> 00:04:21,253
- Jong Hyuk, do you want any? - I'll have some.

121
00:04:21,253 --> 00:04:23,293
The chocolate muffin looks good.

122
00:04:23,463 --> 00:04:24,993
- A chocolate muffin. - Do you want some?

123
00:04:24,993 --> 00:04:26,193
Sure.

124
00:04:26,193 --> 00:04:27,293
Which one do you want?

125
00:04:27,733 --> 00:04:28,963
I'm good.

126
00:04:28,963 --> 00:04:30,003
- Really? - Go ahead.

127
00:04:30,303 --> 00:04:31,973
- I bet you didn't have breakfast. - No, I did.

128
00:04:34,133 --> 00:04:35,703
I...

129
00:04:35,703 --> 00:04:36,703
(He never misses breakfast.)

130
00:04:36,843 --> 00:04:39,743
- Did you have breakfast? - I had chicken breast.

131
00:04:39,973 --> 00:04:41,243
- Are you on a diet? - Do you want some, Jong Hyuk?

132
00:04:41,243 --> 00:04:42,583
Yes. I'm going to start filming...

133
00:04:42,583 --> 00:04:44,913
- this Sunday. - Me too. I have to watch my diet.

134
00:04:44,983 --> 00:04:46,113
- Gosh, this is... - Why are you trying to lose weight?

135
00:04:46,113 --> 00:04:47,383
- You already lost a lot of weight. - You look great.

136
00:04:47,553 --> 00:04:49,483
I did lose, but I gained weight again.

137
00:04:50,123 --> 00:04:52,023
- I'm trying to lose weight again. - You're trying again?

138
00:04:52,023 --> 00:04:53,453
For the past few months,

139
00:04:53,453 --> 00:04:55,893
- I ate everything I wanted. - I see.

140
00:04:56,123 --> 00:04:57,793
So I gained a lot of weight.

141
00:04:57,793 --> 00:05:00,533
- I'll try to lose weight again. - That happens during the holidays.

142
00:05:00,533 --> 00:05:02,103
- Right. - Even if you try...

143
00:05:02,233 --> 00:05:03,233
As I said earlier,
- she's close to Sook. - Yes.

144
00:05:04,603 --> 00:05:05,703
Sook's friend.

145
00:05:06,273 --> 00:05:08,073
- My soulmate. - Sook also introduced you...

146
00:05:08,073 --> 00:05:09,843
to the world of camping.

147
00:05:10,373 --> 00:05:13,373
Actually, when it comes to camping, I know more than her.

148
00:05:13,373 --> 00:05:14,973
(She's been a camper for 17 years.)

149
00:05:14,973 --> 00:05:16,883
Then did you introduce Sook to camping?

150
00:05:17,213 --> 00:05:18,483
I tried to get her to try camping.

151
00:05:18,483 --> 00:05:19,753
- I see. - Really?

152
00:05:19,753 --> 00:05:22,583
For four years, she just came over to my tent...

153
00:05:23,483 --> 00:05:25,423
and enjoyed her time there. She often slept over too.

154
00:05:25,423 --> 00:05:27,123
"Mi Ran, I love it here. My nose feels so fresh."

155
00:05:27,123 --> 00:05:28,693
She'd go back to the city after a few days.

156
00:05:28,823 --> 00:05:31,793
- She now runs a camping channel. - Everyone thinks of camping...

157
00:05:31,793 --> 00:05:33,293
- when they think of Sook now. - Right.

158
00:05:33,663 --> 00:05:35,933
Sook tried to get me to like camping too.

159
00:05:36,263 --> 00:05:38,773
She told me to come and have fun.

160
00:05:39,003 --> 00:05:40,573
- But you hate camping. - So...

161
00:05:40,573 --> 00:05:42,273
- Right. I don't like camping. - You like going to hotels.

162
00:05:42,273 --> 00:05:43,543
My gosh. How did you know?

163
00:05:43,543 --> 00:05:45,313
- Hotels and resorts. - I like going to resorts.

164
00:05:45,713 --> 00:05:47,743
- You like fully equipped places. - Right.

165
00:05:47,743 --> 00:05:48,943
I like calling the front desk...

166
00:05:48,943 --> 00:05:50,783
to order room service and getting the food delivered.

167
00:05:50,783 --> 00:05:52,653
A place I can just go without any preparation.

168
00:05:52,653 --> 00:05:54,713
- I prefer places like that. Right. - They also clean your room.

169
00:05:54,713 --> 00:05:55,883
I love that.

170
00:05:56,083 --> 00:05:57,883
First of all, I hate bugs.

171
00:05:57,883 --> 00:05:59,693
I hate getting mosquito bites.

172
00:06:00,193 --> 00:06:01,853
They're itchy and annoying.

173
00:06:02,093 --> 00:06:04,923
- I don't like being in the wild. - I see.

174
00:06:04,923 --> 00:06:06,063
Wait, did you grow up in Seoul?

175
00:06:06,063 --> 00:06:08,063
- Yes. I did. Why? - I see. Nothing.

176
00:06:08,833 --> 00:06:10,503
- Why do you ask? - Nothing.

177
00:06:10,503 --> 00:06:11,533
(Flustered by the strange question)

178
00:06:11,633 --> 00:06:13,373
Is that why you hate bugs?

179
00:06:13,373 --> 00:06:14,433
- Why do you ask? - Bugs are common...

180
00:06:14,433 --> 00:06:15,503
in the countryside.

181
00:06:16,443 --> 00:06:17,873
- He's not from the countryside. - Well, the thing is...

182
00:06:18,003 --> 00:06:20,143
I can understand why you might think he's not from Seoul.

183
00:06:20,173 --> 00:06:22,243
- But he grew up in Seoul. - He's a Seoulite to the bone.

184
00:06:22,413 --> 00:06:23,913
Which one of you has ties...

185
00:06:23,913 --> 00:06:25,413
- to Paju? - Which one of you is it?

186
00:06:25,413 --> 00:06:27,113
I live in Paju now.

187
00:06:27,113 --> 00:06:28,883
- Here? In Paju? - You live here?

188
00:06:29,323 --> 00:06:31,483
- Really? - It's been over ten years...

189
00:06:31,483 --> 00:06:34,553
- since I moved here. - Really?

190
00:06:34,623 --> 00:06:37,023
- It's been over a decade. - What made you move here?

191
00:06:37,493 --> 00:06:39,363
I was just pushed out to Paju.

192
00:06:39,993 --> 00:06:42,963
- What? You got pushed out here? - I couldn't...

193
00:06:43,463 --> 00:06:45,933
Let me explain.

194
00:06:45,933 --> 00:06:48,133
My husband and I had struggled financially since we were newlyweds.

195
00:06:48,473 --> 00:06:50,173
So when we got married,

196
00:06:50,173 --> 00:06:51,873
- we lived in Ilsan. - Then you moved to Paju.

197
00:06:51,873 --> 00:06:53,813
Then we moved farther away from Seoul.

198
00:06:54,843 --> 00:06:57,513
So we moved to Paju, farther away from Seoul.

199
00:06:57,783 --> 00:06:59,183
But once we moved here,

200
00:06:59,183 --> 00:07:00,613
- we liked living here. - This is a nice place to live.

201
00:07:00,883 --> 00:07:02,323
People who work in our industry...

202
00:07:02,323 --> 00:07:03,723
- can get to Sangam fast. - From Paju.

203
00:07:03,723 --> 00:07:05,693
- The commute got shorter. - There are many filming sets...

204
00:07:05,693 --> 00:07:07,993
- here in Paju. - There are so many sets in Paju.

205
00:07:07,993 --> 00:07:10,023
- Right. - Everything is so closeby...

206
00:07:10,023 --> 00:07:11,493
as long as I don't go..

207
00:07:11,493 --> 00:07:12,963
- to beauty salons. - Right.

208
00:07:12,963 --> 00:07:14,093
It's a great place.

209
00:07:14,233 --> 00:07:16,003
A lot of beauty salons...

210
00:07:16,003 --> 00:07:17,763
- That's right. - are in Gangnam.

211
00:07:17,963 --> 00:07:19,433
That's why I rarely go to beauty salons.

212
00:07:21,173 --> 00:07:22,943
- You are indeed a camper. - Yes.

213
00:07:23,243 --> 00:07:25,143
- You're very practical. - Going there takes up so much time.

214
00:07:25,143 --> 00:07:27,373
- Right. You have to go back too. - Going back and forth... Right.

215
00:07:27,643 --> 00:07:29,083
- Right. - I had to do that today.

216
00:07:29,213 --> 00:07:31,413
- Did you come back from Gangnam? - I went there at 5:20am.

217
00:07:31,413 --> 00:07:33,083
- You were in Gangnam. - Yes. I went to a beauty salon.

218
00:07:33,413 --> 00:07:36,253
I had to go to the beauty salon for this. So I went.

219
00:07:36,353 --> 00:07:37,353
- You went today. - Yes.

220
00:07:37,353 --> 00:07:39,123
All right. We should go...

221
00:07:39,123 --> 00:07:41,523
- and meet Whenever Guests. - Yes, let's go and meet them.

222
00:07:41,523 --> 00:07:43,123
These are our first Whenever Guests.

223
00:07:43,263 --> 00:07:45,163
Nam Kyung Hee and Nam Yu Jin.

224
00:07:45,463 --> 00:07:47,863
"We are sisters who have been guarding the fire that..."

225
00:07:47,863 --> 00:07:50,133
- "has never gone out for a decade." - A fire?

226
00:07:50,833 --> 00:07:52,303
"Even in the biting,"

227
00:07:52,303 --> 00:07:53,773
- "Siberian-like winds of Paju," - Right.

228
00:07:53,773 --> 00:07:56,703
"you must wear short sleeve shirts and shorts here."

229
00:07:57,203 --> 00:07:59,143
"Just three minutes."

230
00:07:59,373 --> 00:08:01,013
"That's all the time you need to be covered in sweat."

231
00:08:01,013 --> 00:08:02,643
"We'd like to invite you..."

232
00:08:02,913 --> 00:08:04,183
- "to our special place." - "A special place?

233
00:08:04,183 --> 00:08:05,853
- It must be a sauna. - It's a sauna.

234
00:08:05,853 --> 00:08:06,913
- The dry sauna. - I see.

235
00:08:07,613 --> 00:08:09,723
- A dry sauna in Paju... - So...

236
00:08:09,723 --> 00:08:12,023
- Is there one? - There's Pine Tree Sauna.

237
00:08:12,083 --> 00:08:14,493
- My gosh. She knows right away. - There are a few more...

238
00:08:15,093 --> 00:08:16,363
saunas.

239
00:08:16,363 --> 00:08:18,623
But a place with a real fire...

240
00:08:18,623 --> 00:08:21,093
- There's a famous place, right? - Yes. There is.

241
00:08:21,563 --> 00:08:23,263
- Today... - Where is it? "Odo-ro."

242
00:08:23,263 --> 00:08:24,803
- I see. - We have a car today.

243
00:08:24,863 --> 00:08:26,003
- Wait. "Odo-ro?" - Do you know this place?

244
00:08:26,703 --> 00:08:28,033
I think I know this place.

245
00:08:28,703 --> 00:08:33,043
- "Odo-ro 130-gil." - This is the place.

246
00:08:33,043 --> 00:08:34,143
- Let's go. - I see.

247
00:08:34,143 --> 00:08:35,373
- I know this place. - Gosh.

248
00:08:35,373 --> 00:08:37,113
- Have you been there? - It's this place.

249
00:08:37,313 --> 00:08:38,743
