1263
00:43:18,910 --> 00:43:20,580
Is it because you're on a diet?

1264
00:43:20,580 --> 00:43:22,380
No, I don't mind.

1265
00:43:22,380 --> 00:43:23,380
I can eat anything.

1266
00:43:23,650 --> 00:43:25,620
I actually had tofu yesterday, so...

1267
00:43:26,690 --> 00:43:28,050
That's why you didn't even mention it.

1268
00:43:28,050 --> 00:43:29,690
This area is well-known for its beans.

1269
00:43:29,690 --> 00:43:30,690
- Oh, that's why... - Then...

1270
00:43:30,690 --> 00:43:33,260
Their beans, tofu, and doenjang are very famous,

1271
00:43:33,330 --> 00:43:34,760
but she skipped them.

1272
00:43:34,760 --> 00:43:37,500
- You had tofu yesterday. - She had it yesterday.

1273
00:43:37,500 --> 00:43:39,130
How about spicy braised chicken?

1274
00:43:39,130 --> 00:43:41,070
Spicy braised chicken with acorn jelly.

1275
00:43:41,770 --> 00:43:43,300
With acorn jelly?

1276
00:43:43,300 --> 00:43:45,940
They make spicy braised chicken using acorn jelly?

1277
00:43:46,570 --> 00:43:47,570
Is that even possible?

1278
00:43:47,570 --> 00:43:49,080
Acorn...

1279
00:43:49,080 --> 00:43:50,540
- Acorn jelly? - Acorn jelly.

1280
00:43:50,540 --> 00:43:52,010
Acorn jelly is a diet food.

1281
00:43:52,010 --> 00:43:54,580
- Yes, it's good for weight loss. - Let's try that, then.

1282
00:43:55,750 --> 00:43:57,320
Let me give them a call.

1283
00:43:57,580 --> 00:43:58,580
- She's calling. - You have to call them?

1284
00:43:58,580 --> 00:44:00,220
I don't know if the owner is in or not.

1285
00:44:00,690 --> 00:44:02,460
You don't go unless the owner is there?

1286
00:44:02,890 --> 00:44:04,390
I didn't know you could book it.

1287
00:44:04,390 --> 00:44:06,860
There are people who only go if the owner is there.

1288
00:44:07,030 --> 00:44:09,460
- They're like, "I'm coming!" - Exactly.

1289
00:44:09,960 --> 00:44:11,660
- The sunlight feels warm. - It does.

1290
00:44:11,660 --> 00:44:12,670
(Calling the owner)

1291
00:44:12,870 --> 00:44:15,630
Are you in the restaurant today?

1292
00:44:16,700 --> 00:44:19,710
I see. I'm filming a show, and I'm taking them with me.

1293
00:44:19,710 --> 00:44:20,710
(Fortunately, the owner is there.)

1294
00:44:21,470 --> 00:44:23,040
- Spicy braised chicken is good. - Regular chicken.

1295
00:44:23,040 --> 00:44:24,210
You prefer regular chicken over Korean native chicken, right?

1296
00:44:24,210 --> 00:44:25,780
- I want regular chicken. - Regular chicken.

1297
00:44:25,780 --> 00:44:26,850
Regular chicken, please.

1298
00:44:28,250 --> 00:44:30,480
- Korean native chicken is stiff. - Yes.

1299
00:44:30,480 --> 00:44:32,420
- It can be. - Right?

1300
00:44:32,420 --> 00:44:33,790
(The man from Seoul prefers tender meat.)

1301
00:44:33,950 --> 00:44:34,990
Okay.

1302
00:44:35,090 --> 00:44:37,020
(She pre-ordered the food on the phone.)

1303
00:44:37,420 --> 00:44:38,560
Do you go there with your family?

1304
00:44:38,690 --> 00:44:39,890
I go with Kim Sook.

1305
00:44:39,890 --> 00:44:41,060
(A place she often goes with Sook)

1306
00:44:41,060 --> 00:44:42,290
I told them,

1307
00:44:42,290 --> 00:44:44,230
so they'll be cooking the chicken.

1308
00:44:44,230 --> 00:44:46,630
Really? We might be able to eat right away.

1309
00:44:48,070 --> 00:44:49,570
I see a lot of cars here.

1310
00:44:49,570 --> 00:44:50,870
This place is...

1311
00:44:50,870 --> 00:44:51,970
It must be a food street.

1312
00:44:52,410 --> 00:44:54,070
- Hold on. - There are so many cars!

1313
00:44:54,070 --> 00:44:55,540
- Goodness. - Yes, there are.

1314
00:44:55,540 --> 00:44:58,180
There must be lots of famous restaurants.

1315
00:44:58,340 --> 00:45:00,750
Do you see the one with the red sign?

1316
00:45:00,750 --> 00:45:01,810
Yes.

1317
00:45:01,880 --> 00:45:03,820
- It smells so delicious. - This place is...

1318
00:45:03,820 --> 00:45:04,980
I know, right?

1319
00:45:05,650 --> 00:45:07,750
- It does. - I mean, the whole neighborhood...

1320
00:45:07,750 --> 00:45:08,790
- smells delicious. - I could smell it instantly.

1321
00:45:08,790 --> 00:45:11,220
A lot of top-rated restaurants are gathered here.

1322
00:45:11,790 --> 00:45:13,290
It's packed with famous restaurants.

1323
00:45:13,660 --> 00:45:15,760
At the foot of the mountain.

1324
00:45:16,000 --> 00:45:17,000
Oh, the mountain.

1325
00:45:17,130 --> 00:45:19,500
Oh, this must be Mount Samhak!

1326
00:45:19,500 --> 00:45:20,870
- Mount Simhak. - Mount Simhak.

1327
00:45:22,270 --> 00:45:23,270
- What was that name? - Mount Samhak?
(He fails to act like he knows.)

1328
00:45:24,270 --> 00:45:26,440
- This is Mount Samhak, no, Simhak. - Simhak.

1329
00:45:26,440 --> 00:45:27,910
Where all the top-rated restaurants are.

1330
00:45:27,910 --> 00:45:29,510
- Exactly. - I see.

1331
00:45:29,680 --> 00:45:30,980
I didn't...

1332
00:45:31,080 --> 00:45:32,850
- They have many good restaurants. - So, it's already famous.

1333
00:45:32,850 --> 00:45:33,980
- It is. - Really?

1334
00:45:33,980 --> 00:45:35,710
- No bad restaurant can last... - It's well-known.

1335
00:45:35,710 --> 00:45:37,720
- in this area. - I see.

1336
00:45:37,720 --> 00:45:40,020
So, this is Mount Simhak.

1337
00:45:40,350 --> 00:45:42,760
It's such an old shop.

1338
00:45:43,060 --> 00:45:44,190
- Hello. - Hello.

1339
00:45:44,190 --> 00:45:45,690
- Should we go inside? - Hello.

1340
00:45:46,260 --> 00:45:47,390
Good afternoon.

1341
00:45:47,790 --> 00:45:49,260
I've been here with Sung Min.

1342
00:45:49,260 --> 00:45:50,960
- Right? Who? - Yes.

1343
00:45:50,960 --> 00:45:52,930
- Lee Sung Min. - Oh, Lee Sung Min.

1344
00:45:53,970 --> 00:45:55,800
You called them in advance, so we can eat...

1345
00:45:56,300 --> 00:45:57,570
- She did. - right away.

1346
00:45:58,140 --> 00:46:00,240
It takes like two hours if you come in and order.

1347
00:46:01,570 --> 00:46:03,710
It feels so good to eat after a success.

1348
00:46:03,710 --> 00:46:04,710
I know, right?

1349
00:46:05,010 --> 00:46:07,510
- But you're doing this every week. - It feels good.

1350
00:46:07,510 --> 00:46:09,250
- We do. - It's so fun.

1351
00:46:11,550 --> 00:46:13,090
It looks good. I've never had spicy braised chicken...

1352
00:46:13,090 --> 00:46:14,650
with acorn jelly in it.

1353
00:46:14,650 --> 00:46:15,650
(The spicy braised chicken starts boiling.)

1354
00:46:16,690 --> 00:46:18,960
- It looks tasty. - Can we get some ramyeon?

1355
00:46:18,960 --> 00:46:19,990
Here it is.

1356
00:46:20,190 --> 00:46:21,330
We have to put it in.

1357
00:46:22,060 --> 00:46:23,730
- After we eat the bits. - Yes, after.

1358
00:46:23,960 --> 00:46:25,700
I wonder what the acorn jelly tastes like.

1359
00:46:25,700 --> 00:46:27,300
Do you want to taste it?

1360
00:46:27,300 --> 00:46:28,800
- Have one, Jae Suk. - I'll have one.

1361
00:46:29,570 --> 00:46:32,400
(Trying the acorn jelly they were most curious about)

1362
00:46:33,810 --> 00:46:35,910
The acorn jelly tastes good.

1363
00:46:37,640 --> 00:46:38,740
It actually tastes like acorns.

1364
00:46:38,910 --> 00:46:40,480
- It's good. - When you buy them at the store,

1365
00:46:40,480 --> 00:46:41,780
they don't taste like acorns.

1366
00:46:41,780 --> 00:46:43,620
- The bitter acorn taste. - Yes.

1367
00:46:43,980 --> 00:46:45,950
When you make acorn jelly wrong,

1368
00:46:45,950 --> 00:46:48,050
- the aftertaste is bitter. - Right.

1369
00:46:48,050 --> 00:46:49,920
- But this is... - But the bitter...

1370
00:46:50,320 --> 00:46:51,420
The bitter taste is from acorns.

1371
00:46:51,420 --> 00:46:53,160
I don't like it when it's too bitter, though.

1372
00:46:54,060 --> 00:46:55,430
- This is perfect for me. - Is it?

1373
00:46:55,960 --> 00:46:57,460
- I'm glad. - I wouldn't have eaten it, then.

1374
00:46:57,460 --> 00:46:58,460
(This Seoul man doesn't like bitterness.)

1375
00:46:58,460 --> 00:46:59,470
If it's too bitter.

1376
00:46:59,470 --> 00:47:01,100
- You like sweet food too. - Yes.

1377
00:47:02,100 --> 00:47:03,570
The chicken is all cooked now.

1378
00:47:03,940 --> 00:47:06,270
- You can eat it. - It's good.

1379
00:47:06,410 --> 00:47:07,510
It looks scrumptious.

1380
00:47:07,670 --> 00:47:09,680
- Look at the color. - It's insane.

1381
00:47:09,680 --> 00:47:11,980
(He blows on it and takes a bite.)

1382
00:47:12,650 --> 00:47:15,310
- It's delicious. - Yes.

1383
00:47:17,780 --> 00:47:19,490
- This is insane. - The color is...

1384
00:47:20,790 --> 00:47:22,350
(Jong Hyuk starts with a sip of hot soup.)

1385
00:47:22,350 --> 00:47:24,090
I felt too hot earlier.

1386
00:47:24,860 --> 00:47:26,460
The heat was like...

1387
00:47:26,460 --> 00:47:28,230
- It's spicy. - Cucumber helps.

1388
00:47:28,590 --> 00:47:29,800
I've never had them,

1389
00:47:30,230 --> 00:47:32,060
- but they grew on me. - Can you handle spicy food?

1390
00:47:32,060 --> 00:47:33,100
- Me? - Yes.

1391
00:47:33,100 --> 00:47:34,470
- Not really. - Me neither.

1392
00:47:35,270 --> 00:47:36,440
You guys are spicy food wimps.

1393
00:47:37,040 --> 00:47:38,800
- I wouldn't call myself that. - Me neither.

1394
00:47:38,800 --> 00:47:40,640
But my stomach hurts the next day.

1395
00:47:40,640 --> 00:47:41,810
- I see. - Everyone does.

1396
00:47:42,210 --> 00:47:43,940
- It's tasty, though. - It is.

1397
00:47:44,410 --> 00:47:45,410
Right?

1398
00:47:46,150 --> 00:47:47,510
The noodles got thicker.

1399
00:47:47,510 --> 00:47:49,520
It looks good. It's like tteokbokki with ramyeon.

1400
00:47:49,520 --> 00:47:51,250
- It is. - That looks so tasty.

1401
00:47:51,250 --> 00:47:52,350
It's gotten so thick.

1402
00:47:52,920 --> 00:47:54,420
Diet is out of the question now.

1403
00:47:54,420 --> 00:47:55,890
- This ramyeon... - It has been cooked well.

1404
00:47:56,390 --> 00:47:57,860
- This is... - It's too good.

1405
00:47:57,990 --> 00:47:59,060
No!

1406
00:47:59,190 --> 00:48:00,290
- It's way too good. - Not that.

1407
00:48:00,290 --> 00:48:01,290
- This is... - Not ramyeon.

1408
00:48:01,290 --> 00:48:04,060
- Not ramyeon. - This is...

1409
00:48:04,200 --> 00:48:05,500
- Please. - They say you don't gain weight...

1410
00:48:05,500 --> 00:48:06,800
if you enjoy the food.

1411
00:48:06,800 --> 00:48:08,000
(Whatever.)

1412
00:48:08,000 --> 00:48:09,270
Just go on a run after.

1413
00:48:09,970 --> 00:48:11,040
You can run.

1414
00:48:12,040 --> 00:48:14,270
(Tearing up)

1415
00:48:14,610 --> 00:48:15,610
Jae Suk.

1416
00:48:16,240 --> 00:48:17,280
It's good, isn't it?

1417
00:48:17,980 --> 00:48:19,650
- It's good, isn't it? - It's too good.

1418
00:48:21,580 --> 00:48:23,520
I think it's been a while since I last had ramyeon.

1419
00:48:24,180 --> 00:48:25,850
It's so good. It goes so well...

1420
00:48:26,050 --> 00:48:27,350
with the sauce.

1421
00:48:27,350 --> 00:48:29,520
(Jong Hyuk also indulges in some carbs.)

1422
00:48:29,990 --> 00:48:31,120
So good.

1423
00:48:31,560 --> 00:48:33,660
- It's tasty. - It's a special soy sauce.

1424
00:48:33,760 --> 00:48:34,960
I think it's homemade.

1425
00:48:35,460 --> 00:48:38,060
They add perilla oil and stuff, so it's good.

1426
00:48:38,060 --> 00:48:39,100
It's great.

1427
00:48:39,930 --> 00:48:40,930
It's very good.

1428
00:48:40,930 --> 00:48:42,740
(Mi Ran takes a big bite of acorn jelly.)

1429
00:48:44,940 --> 00:48:47,810
The taste of that ramyeon won't go away.

1430
00:48:47,810 --> 00:48:49,740
- Have some more. - Have some. You've already eaten.

1431
00:48:49,740 --> 00:48:51,440
- Right. You've already eaten. - Yes.

1432
00:48:51,810 --> 00:48:52,810
Here.

1433
00:48:52,810 --> 00:48:55,550
If you offer me more, I can't refuse.

1434
00:48:55,550 --> 00:48:57,320
- This is it. - Here.

1435
00:48:57,320 --> 00:48:58,550
- Just this. - No, this is it.

1436
00:48:58,550 --> 00:48:59,550
(He doesn't refuse the second time.)

1437
00:48:59,550 --> 00:49:01,650
- Have that. - It's less than a bite.

1438
00:49:01,650 --> 00:49:02,660
She's right.

1439
00:49:03,290 --> 00:49:05,620
- It won't make a huge difference. - I'll work out hard tomorrow.

1440
00:49:06,460 --> 00:49:07,890
Do you normally not eat these?

1441
00:49:07,930 --> 00:49:09,430
Do you only eat chicken breasts?

1442
00:49:09,430 --> 00:49:11,060
No, I don't do that.

1443
00:49:11,300 --> 00:49:13,470
But the first shoot is in two days.

1444
00:49:13,470 --> 00:49:14,630
I see.

1445
00:49:15,370 --> 00:49:17,740
- Since last week, - Then, you should be careful.

1446
00:49:17,740 --> 00:49:19,610
I've been pretty nervous.

1447
00:49:19,610 --> 00:49:20,810
Skip dinner today.

1448
00:49:23,210 --> 00:49:24,940
That's the thing with first shoots.

1449
00:49:24,940 --> 00:49:26,610
- Right. - It feels...

1450
00:49:26,610 --> 00:49:28,280
- It makes you mindful. - like I'm taking a test.

1451
00:49:28,280 --> 00:49:29,350
- And I can't sleep well. - Right.

1452
00:49:30,950 --> 00:49:32,850
Once you get the feel...

1453
00:49:32,850 --> 00:49:35,020
of the atmosphere of the film site,

1454
00:49:35,290 --> 00:49:37,160
you return to your normal self.

1455
00:49:37,360 --> 00:49:38,920
It always feels new and thrilling.

1456
00:49:39,060 --> 00:49:40,160
- Does it? - Yes.

1457
00:49:41,890 --> 00:49:43,160
I haven't had acorn jelly in so long.

1458
00:49:43,160 --> 00:49:44,160
(Staring)

1459
00:49:44,330 --> 00:49:45,330
As a side dish...

1460
00:49:45,330 --> 00:49:46,630
Did you do any martial arts?

1461
00:49:46,630 --> 00:49:47,700
(Conditions for a Dine and Dash)

1462
00:49:47,800 --> 00:49:48,930
"Conditions for a Dine and Dash?" What's that?

1463
00:49:48,930 --> 00:49:51,670
To dine and dash, you must have a tenth-degree black belt.

1464
00:49:52,300 --> 00:49:54,770
- Tenth-degree. - Taekwon, judo, hapkido, and kendo?

1465
00:49:54,770 --> 00:49:56,940
- What about you? - I did taekwondo.

1466
00:49:56,940 --> 00:49:58,440
- Taekwondo. Which degree? - Yes.

1467
00:49:58,710 --> 00:50:00,880
Fourth-degree. My father runs a gym.

1468
00:50:01,280 --> 00:50:02,610
- A taekwondo gym. - Really?

1469
00:50:03,550 --> 00:50:05,120
He has many unexpected records.

1470
00:50:05,120 --> 00:50:06,290
What else?

1471
00:50:06,520 --> 00:50:08,150
I lived in the Philippines...

1472
00:50:08,150 --> 00:50:10,490
- and moved to New Zealand. - Really?

1473
00:50:10,490 --> 00:50:12,090
I moved to New Zealand when I was in middle school.

1474
00:50:12,090 --> 00:50:13,890
And I majored in hotel management.

1475
00:50:13,890 --> 00:50:15,060
I did.

1476
00:50:15,160 --> 00:50:17,530
I wanted to be a bartender on a cruise.

1477
00:50:17,530 --> 00:50:18,530
I see.

1478
00:50:18,530 --> 00:50:21,300
So, I was a bartender in Cheongdam-dong for a while.

1479
00:50:21,300 --> 00:50:22,870
- You actually worked as one? - I did.

1480
00:50:22,870 --> 00:50:25,270
- It was your job? - It was. Not a part-time job.

1481
00:50:25,640 --> 00:50:28,210
- What made you start acting? - I was working,

1482
00:50:28,470 --> 00:50:31,440
and MBC moved to its new company building.

1483
00:50:31,440 --> 00:50:33,710
- In Sangam. - And as they did,

1484
00:50:33,710 --> 00:50:35,750
they wanted to film a promotional video.

1485
00:50:35,750 --> 00:50:37,780
I played an extra who had to run around...

1486
00:50:37,780 --> 00:50:39,250
carrying a red box for two weeks.

1487
00:50:40,020 --> 00:50:42,250
It was pretty fun, so...

1488
00:50:43,260 --> 00:50:44,860
So, you quit your bartender job.

1489
00:50:44,860 --> 00:50:47,760
A part-timer there was an actor,

1490
00:50:47,760 --> 00:50:50,160
so I asked him, "I want to try acting."

1491
00:50:50,160 --> 00:50:51,960
"How do I start?" He said,

1492
00:50:52,100 --> 00:50:53,570
"Do you want to move in with me?"

1493
00:50:53,570 --> 00:50:55,400
- I lived with him for seven years. - As roommates.

1494
00:50:55,400 --> 00:50:57,640
Yes. We lived in a studio apartment. We only had one room.

1495
00:50:57,640 --> 00:50:58,800
We slept on a bunk bed.

1496
00:50:59,170 --> 00:51:00,740
His name is Jang Jae Ho,

1497
00:51:00,740 --> 00:51:02,670
and he married actress Gong Min Jeong.

1498
00:51:02,670 --> 00:51:05,380
- Really? - I'm friends with her too,

1499
00:51:05,380 --> 00:51:06,780
so I gave a congratulatory speech at their wedding.

1500
00:51:07,150 --> 00:51:10,820
I parodied "I Believe" in the middle...

1501
00:51:11,050 --> 00:51:12,850
and copied the famous scene.

1502
00:51:12,920 --> 00:51:14,190
I had written the script.

1503
00:51:14,190 --> 00:51:15,650
The song started playing,

1504
00:51:15,650 --> 00:51:17,520
- and I was moved to tears. - You cried?

1505
00:51:17,790 --> 00:51:19,190
I wailed there.

1506
00:51:19,990 --> 00:51:21,460
"My brother is..."

1507
00:51:21,790 --> 00:51:24,530
People asked if I was his ex-boyfriend.

1508
00:51:24,830 --> 00:51:26,700
(His tears misled people.)

1509
00:51:26,830 --> 00:51:29,700
- You must be rooting for him. - I always cry at weddings now.

1510
00:51:30,100 --> 00:51:31,400
- Why? - I'm so thankful for him.

1511
00:51:31,400 --> 00:51:35,010
I just automatically cry when I watch weddings.

1512
00:51:35,010 --> 00:51:36,380
So do I.

1513
00:51:36,380 --> 00:51:37,380
(Tearing up)

1514
00:51:37,510 --> 00:51:38,640
Are you a feeler?

1515
00:51:38,880 --> 00:51:40,610
- I'm a thinker. - You're lying.

1516
00:51:40,610 --> 00:51:41,610
I'm a total thinker.

1517
